    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/lang/Math.html#ceil(double)\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>Math.ceil()</code></a> is the correct function to call. I'm guessing <code>a</code> is an <code>int</code>, which would make <code>a / 100</code> perform integer arithmetic. Try <code>Math.ceil(a / 100.0)</code> instead.</p>\n\n<pre><code>int a = 142;\nSystem.out.println(a / 100);\nSystem.out.println(Math.ceil(a / 100));\nSystem.out.println(a / 100.0);\nSystem.out.println(Math.ceil(a / 100.0));\nSystem.out.println((int) Math.ceil(a / 100.0));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Outputs:</p>\n\n<pre><code>1\n1.0\n1.42\n2.0\n2\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>See <a href=\"http://ideone.com/yhT0l\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://ideone.com/yhT0l</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "user_type" : "does_not_exist",
      "display_name" : "user467871"
