  "title" : "Java Round up Any Number",
  "body" : "<p>I can't seem to find the answer I'm looking for regarding a simple question: how do I round up any number to the nearest <code>int</code>?</p>\n\n<p>For example, whenever the number is 0.2, 0.7, 0.2222, 0.4324, 0.99999 I would want the outcome to be 1.</p>\n\n<p>So far I have</p>\n\n<pre><code>int b = (int) Math.ceil(a / 100);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It doesn't seem to be doing the job, though.</p>\n"
